g.title: EleanorRank5Convo8 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank5Convo8 begins.

g.title: j1958707260
g.text: I’ve been thinking. There’s something I need to do.

g.title: j1029272499
g.text: I’m going to need help.

g.title: j2200730001
g.text: Always here for you. What’s on your mind?

g.title: j3486440719
g.text: Can't chat right now, sorry. [End.]

g.title: j2445443260
g.text: Check boolean EleanorChristopher2

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3779683123
g.text: So. Christopher.

g.title: j2445443260->j3779683123
g.text: true

g.title: j167143005
g.text: Check boolean EleanorChristopher1

g.title: j2445443260->j167143005
g.text: false

g.title: j2871451739
g.text: I’ve been holding on to him for years. So has Arthur. We have a ritual every year in his memory. But not this year. I couldn't face it.

g.title: j1038573988
g.text: To... make a very long and tragic story very short... Christopher died in a roadside bomb before we were married.

g.title: j167143005->j1038573988
g.text: true

g.title: j2110926
g.text: It's time I told you about Christopher.

g.title: j167143005->j2110926
g.text: false

g.title: j3632204346
g.text: I don’t know whether ghosts exist, but they might as well, because I’ve let him become one.

g.title: j3540900366
g.text: Perhaps I'll tell you the whole story another day. Perhaps I won't.

g.title: j1470883197
g.text: Arthur's best friend. We were engaged. I thought I was in love with him.

g.title: j3789603794
g.text: Don’t be so hard on yourself. You were in love with the guy.

g.title: j1010202521
g.text: I'm telling you all this now because...

g.title: j874244672
g.text: Boolean EleanorChristopher1 is now true.

g.title: j2052270870
g.text: Oh mate. I THOUGHT I was. I loved him, but I didn’t even know if I was IN love with him or not.

g.title: j2346217618
g.text: Boolean EleanorChristopher2 is now true.

g.title: j1358148024
g.text: That sounds awful, doesn’t it? It’s true, though. At the time, it just didn’t seem important. Then he died, and that became what our story was all about.

g.title: j592888296
g.text: Everything that I admired about him has just been overshadowed by how he died. I can’t think about him without this knot tightening in my stomach.

g.title: j2649506268
g.text: It’s not fair. TO HIM. He deserves better than that.

g.title: j1560594889
g.text: I understand. Totally. I made a choice to remember my parents the way they deserved.

g.title: j2163957951
g.text: What happened was terrible. There’s no getting around it. But we can’t let that be the only thing we hold on to.

g.title: j3661988910
g.text: So why do I feel so guilty?

g.title: j1015322489
g.text: Why do I feel like letting him go is the same thing as throwing him away?

g.title: j3154807768
g.text: Because you’ve carried him for so long you don’t know how to stop.

g.title: j2227822109
g.text: Because you're worried no one else would ever be capable of loving you.

g.title: j741693189
g.text: Gods. You’re bloody right, you know.

g.title: j2999255483
g.text: Check boolean EleanorDating

g.title: j3020847419
g.text: We’re useless at dealing with this, my lot. We bottle everything up. We put a brave face on and whistle in the trenches. It gets us through, just like it got our parents through. But we don’t know how to stop.

g.title: j1693895162
g.text: Is that it? Am I that shallow?

g.title: j2999255483->j1693895162
g.text: true

g.title: j859063509
g.text: I doubt even Christopher would love me in my current condition.

g.title: j2999255483->j859063509
g.text: false

g.title: j526280848
g.text: What should I do? How do I let go?

g.title: j2863958418
g.text: I don't feel I deserve EITHER of you right now

g.title: j480593750
g.text: ... no. That's not fair. I'm not being fair to him at all, am I?

g.title: j3258575278
g.text: Check boolean LettieDiasdeMuertos

g.title: j2396247721
g.text: I think... I want you to have ALL of me. I can't hold back part of myself in a state of endless mourning.

g.title: j3133698711
g.text: He wouldn't want to stand in the way of my happiness. He was kind.

g.title: j1862486729
g.text: I actually think Lettie could help.

g.title: j3258575278->j1862486729
g.text: true

g.title: j1540526694
g.text: You could write him a letter.

g.title: j3258575278->j1540526694
g.text: true

g.title: j3258575278->j1540526694
g.text: false

g.title: j1197187631
g.text: Talk to Arthur, maybe. He's been going through this grief with you from the start.

g.title: j3258575278->j1197187631
g.text: true

g.title: j3258575278->j1197187631
g.text: false

g.title: j1058593586
g.text: Lettie?

g.title: j2911944559
g.text: Part of me thinks that's a stupid idea. He won't read it. He's dead. But...

g.title: j2484384885
g.text: Yes, he has. Maybe that's part of the problem. I know he's upset that I didn't keep up our little ceremony of remembrance this year.

g.title: j3135050883
g.text: Why her?

g.title: j1396553507
g.text: ... the more I think about it, the less stupid it seems.

g.title: j3282795898
g.text: I just... have to say goodbye to Christopher MY way this time. Once and for all.

g.title: j1641377521
g.text: She has a lot of experience. She knows all about commemorating the dead.

g.title: j3610830407
g.text: Yes. I'll do it. There are things I need to say to him. Things I never said when he was alive. Maybe then he can rest.

g.title: j168835860
g.text: To Arthur he'll always be a lost brother, a fallen soldier. That's the mourning he knows and understands. But it's not mine.

g.title: j1056925668
g.text: I’m sure if you asked her for advice, respectfully, she wouldn’t turn you away.

g.title: j2166428073
g.text: Thank you for listening, and for the advice.

g.title: j3587954516
g.text: I can't do it Arthur's way any more. I think... if I just tell him that, he'll get it.

g.title: j2842161792
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j3565331755
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j509875692
g.text: Yes.

g.title: j3720374042
g.text: I will never, ever forget this.

g.title: j1572129716
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j1724367567
g.text: It’s time.

g.title: j3837617298
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j3854917844
g.text: I think I need to let go of a LOT of things.

g.title: j3156085677
g.text: Let me talk to her. If she tells me to piss off, then so be it. But at least I’ll have tried, right?

g.title: j709714282
g.text: It’s got to be worth a try. Lettie’s not as heartless as people think.

g.title: j514719483
g.text: I bet. Living like this, doing what we do every day, we all put up walls. We just forgot to put doors in them.

g.title: j2985337510
g.text: Thank you for beating your lovely head against my wall.
